Except as otherwise provided in this section, the following buildings, or additions to existing buildings, classified by use group shall require the services of an architect licensed in the Commonwealth of Kentucky;
Assembly use group having a capacity of one hundred (100) persons or more, except church buildings having a capacity of four hundred (400) persons or less or six thousand (6,000) square feet or less;
Business use group having a capacity of one hundred (100) persons or more;
Institutional use group, regardless of capacity;
Mercantile use group having a capacity of one hundred (100) persons or more;
Residential use group of more than twelve (12) dwelling units or having a capacity of fifty (50) persons or more;
Educational use groups regardless of capacity; and
Mixed use group containing one (1) or more of the use group classifications and capacities listed under paragraphs (a) through (f) of this subsection.

The following buildings and additions to existing buildings, classified by use group, shall require the services of either an architect or a professional engineer registered in the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
Factory and industrial use group having a capacity of one hundred (100) persons or more;
High hazard use group, regardless of capacity;
Storage use group having a capacity of one hundred (100) persons or more; and
Utility and miscellaneous use groups having a capacity of one hundred (100) persons or more.
